# Generic ignore-list for ad-hoc compliance / secret scanners that don't
# already understand the project layout. Hand to your scanner tooling
# (e.g. `--exclude-from .compliance-ignore`) when its keyword set flags
# transitive npm package names or build artefacts.

# Lockfiles list third-party npm packages by name. `@inquirer/password`
# is one such transitive dep (a sub-package of @inquirer/prompts pulled
# in by @angular/cli) — it is not a credential.
frontend/package-lock.json
backend/package-lock.json

# Coverage reports are regenerated by `npm test --coverage` and contain
# function names from the original source tree before any rename.
backend/coverage/
frontend/coverage/

# Built artefacts
backend/dist/
frontend/dist/
.angular/
